Prefix conventions for ~/.bashrc.d/ snippets.

A snippet may only depend on snippets at lower-numbered levels.
Snippets at the same level must not depend on each other.

Levels 10-40 must use only bash builtins, coreutils, grep, sed, and
findutils (find/xargs). Nothing else.

20  Pure exports of variables and functions. No dependencies, no side effects.
30  Pure exports.
40  Side effects allowed (sources files, mkdir, shopt, etc). Bash builtins,
    coreutils, grep, sed, findutils only.
50  Third-party tool integration guarded by `command -v`. Base level for
    command-v-guarded snippets.
60  Same as 50, but for snippets that depend on another command-v-guarded
    snippet (a 50-level snippet).
80  Must run last (e.g. starship prompt init, kitty integration).
